"feminine noun","usage":"kid(1x)"},"H1430":{"id":"H1430","lemma":"גָּדִישׁ","translit":"gâdîysh","pron":"gaw-deesh'","derivation":"from an unused root (meaning to heap up);","strongs_def":"a stack of sheaves; by analogy, a tomb","kjv_def":"shock (stack) (of corn), tomb.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"shock(2x), stack(1x), tomb(1x)"},"H1431":{"id":"H1431","lemma":"גָּדַל","translit":"gâdal","pron":"gaw-dal'","derivation":"a primitive root; properly, to twist (compare H1434 (גְּדִל)), i.e.","strongs_def":"to be (causatively make) large (in various senses, as in body, mind, estate or honor, also in pride)","kjv_def":"advance, boast, bring up, exceed, excellent, be(-come, do, give, make, wax), great(-er, come to... estate, [phrase] things), grow(up), increase, lift up, magnify(-ifical), be much set by, nourish (up), pass, promote, proudly (spoken), tower.","pos":"verb","usage":"magnify(32x), great(26x), grow(14x), greater(5x)"},"H1432":{"id":"H1432","lemma":"גָּדֵל","translit":"gâdêl","pron":"gaw-dale'","derivation":"from H1431 (גָּדַל);","strongs_def":"large (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"great, grew.","pos":"adjective, participle","usage":"grow(2x), great(2x)"},"H1433":{"id":"H1433","lemma":"גֹּדֶל","translit":"gôdel","pron":"go'-del","derivation":"from H1431 (גָּדַל);","strongs_def":"magnitude (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"greatness, stout(-ness).","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"greatness(11x), stout(1x), stoutness(1x)"},"H1434":{"id":"H1434","lemma":"גְּדִל","translit":"gᵉdil","pron":"ghed-eel'","derivation":"from H1431 (גָּדַל) (in the sense of twisting);","strongs_def":"thread, i.e. a tassel or festoon","kjv_def":"fringe, wreath.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"fringe(1x), wreath(1x)"},"H1435":{"id":"H1435","lemma":"גִּדֵּל","translit":"Giddêl","pron":"ghid-dale'","derivation":"from H1431 (גָּדַל); stout;","strongs_def":"Giddel, the name of one of the Nethinim, also of one of 'Solomon's servants'","kjv_def":"Giddel.","pos":"proper masculine 